rl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aSeit der „Rückkehr des Autors“ gewinnen Fragen literarischer und wissenschaftlicher Autorschaft wieder an Bedeutung. Der vorliegende Band bereitet die seitdem erschienene Forschungsliteratur anschaulich auf und erschließt in historischen und systematischen Fallstudien Theorien und Praktiken der Autorschaft zwischen Hermeneutik und Poststrukturalismus, Narratologie und (Auto-)Fiktionstheorie, Gattungswissen und Inszenierungsstrategien.  aSince the “return of the author,” questions of literary and scientific authorship have been garnering more attention. This volume clearly presents the research literature in this field, and describes theories and practices of authorship through historical and systematic case studies from the perspectives of hermeneutics, poststructuralism, narratology, fiction theory, genre studies, and staging strategies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAuthorship. 4aAutor. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aLiterary scholars.1 aBaßler, Moritz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertschy, Eva-Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDueck, Evelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlauser, Nina Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuttzeit, Gero, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGötze, Clemens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorn, Mirjam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJannidis, Fotis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlausnitzer, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrekn